title: Happy Birdy to You/Daffy Psychic: New Love/Spring Forward, Fall Flat
description: Sylvester crashes Tweety's birthday party. Daffy sees the future. Wile E. Coyote puts a spring in his step.

title: Emotional Support Duck/End of the Leash Gags: Tennis/Adopt Me
description: Porky pretends Daffy is his emotional support duck. Foghorn plays a painful game of tennis. Charlie Dog lets everyone know he's the greatest dog ever.

title: Frame the Feline/Daffy Traffic Cop Stop: Boating License/Unlucky Strikes
description: Hubie and Bertie risk it all to break into a cheese shop. Daffy's drive is disrupted. Porky teaches his nephew to bowl.

title: Fowl Ploy/Sword Loser
description: Instead of flying south for the winter, Daffy finds a cozy home with Elmer. Yosemite Sam stands to become king if he can pull the sword from the stone… or just steal it from Bugs Bunny.

title: Blunder Arrest/Telephone Pole Gag: Airplane Stairs/Cymbal Minded
description: Elmer Fudd tries to arrest Bugs Bunny. Sylvester tries to eat Tweety. Daffy makes sweet, sweet music.

title: Stained By Me/Pilgwim's Pwogwess
description: Daffy ruins Porky's shirt and then ruins Porky's life. Bugs is not very thankful for Pilgrim Elmer's first Thanksgiving celebration.

title: Hook Line and Stinker!/  Balloon Salesman: Everything Pops/  Don't Treadmill on Me
description: Yosemite Sam goes fishing but only catches trouble. Porky's problems start ballooning. Daffy finds himself in a home gym jam.

title: Nip and Duck/Telephone Pole Gag 2: Circular Fan/Asphalt and Battery
description: Daffy Duck learns he's a truly terrible tailor. Sylvester is a fan of great food. Wile E. Coyote's new machine can make roads, but can it also make dinner?

title: Poolside Pest Put the Cat Out: Inside Out Bulls-eye Bunny
description: Daffy helps Elmer relax at the pool. Sylvester won't let Porky sleep. Bugs helps Yosemite Sam put on a knife throwing show.

title: Mt. Neverest/Telephone Pole Gag: Zip Line / Fast & Steady
description: Porky and Daffy go mountain climbing. Sylvester zips out for a quick meal. Wile E. Coyote sees a sign.

title: Rage Rover/To Hive and to Hold/Battle Stations
description: Marvin the Martian proves no match for NASA's Mars Rover. Taz learns about bees… the hard way. Porky and Daffy can't agree on a radio station.

title: Feather of the Bride Daffy Magician: Pick A Card Bugs Hole Gags 2: Rattlesnakes
description: Foghorn Leghorn attempts to charm his future father-in-law. Daffy does a card trick. Elmer discovers a scaly surprise.

title: Grand Canyon Canary/  Hole in Dumb
description: While Tweety Bird goes to the Grand Canyon, Sylvester goes after Tweety. Elmer Fudd wants to play golf, but doesn't want Daffy to be his caddy

title: Bathy Daffy/End of the Leash: Bullseye Painting/Rabbit Sandwich Maker/Put the Cat Out: Window
description: It's bath time for Daffy Duck. The Barnyard Dog is fit to be tied. After inventing a machine that makes Rabbit Sandwiches, Elmer sets out to find a rabbit.

title: Skyscraper Scrap/Balloon Salesman: Feeling Down/The Devil and the Deep Blue Sea
description: Sylvester chases a sky-high snack. Daffy's business feels the effects of inflation. Taz sets sail on a cargo ship… handle with care!

title: Red, White and Bruised/Beaky Buzzard Gags: Bunny/Jet Porkpelled
description: Tweety Bird builds a nest in a military base to keep safe from Sylvester. Beaky Buzzard goes hunting. Porky tries Daffy Duck's new jet pack.

title: Pain Rent/ Nest Effort
description: Bugs' new roommate is a big, big problem. Daffy builds a nest in Elmer's satellite dish

title: Booby Prize/End of the Leash Gags: Pea Shooter/Balloon Salesman: Porky's Head
description: Daffy wants to be watched during Elmer's birdwatching session. Foghorn Leghorn won't let sleeping dogs lie. Porky gets a big head.

title: Ring Master Disaster/ Put the Cat Out: Eyeball/ Pain Event
description: Yosemite Sam can tame a lion, but he can't tame Bugs. Sylvester struggles to stay outside through the night. Porky can't believe he agreed to participate in a boxing match.

title: Crumb and Get It/ Bugs Hole Gags 2: Mini Bugs/ Construction Obstruction
description: In a fight between Porky and Daffy, the birds win. Elmer becomes an outdoorsman. Bugs' burrow is a hot property.

title: Drum Schtick!/ Bugs Hole Gags 2: Frisbee/ Beast A-Birdin
description: Daffy ruins Elmer's camping trip. Bugs' hole flies. Sylvester thinks he's stumbled upon an all-you-can-eat bird buffet.

title: Bone Head/Relax
description: A dog uncovers trouble when he buries a bone in Bugs Bunny's hole. Porky Pig wants to relax, but his nephew Cicero is visiting.

title: Lesson Plan 9 from Outer Space/ Balloon Salesman: Baboon/ Portal Kombat
description: Marvin the Martian has conquered Earth… but no one bothered to tell Bugs. Daffy Duck becomes a balloon salesman. Wile E. Coyote uses sci-fi portals to catch Roadrunner.

title: Battle of the Bunk/End of the Leash Gag: Pull the Carpet Out/Hot Air Buffoon
description: Porky and Daffy get a new bunk bed. Foghorn Leghorn keeps the Barnyard Dog out of reach. Sylvester and Tweety Bird take a ride in a hot air balloon.

title: Practical Jerk/  Bottoms Up
description: Daffy plays one too many pranks on Porky. Bugs has Pete Puma over for dinner.

title: Rotund Rabbit/Hog Wash
description: After stuffing himself with carrots, a big, round Bugs rolls over Elmer. Porky Pig takes a very painful trip through an automated car wash.

title: Pardon the Garden/Put the Cat Out: Flat on the Door/Downward Duck
description: Petunia Pig wants to garden, but all she grows is trouble! Sylvester is a-door-able. Yoga is relaxing - unless Daffy is your instructor.

title: Cro-Mag Numb Skulls/Trophy Hunter
description: Daffy the Caveduck and Prehistoric Porky have a Stone Age adventure. When Elmer goes hunting, he ends up catching a trophy!

title: Virtual Mortality/Daffy Traffic Cop Stop: Lions/Miner Threat
description: Elmer Fudd tries virtual reality. Porky's on patrol. Coal mining is dangerous, especially when you're a canary… and Sylvester is trying to eat you.

title: Livin' the Daydream/ Duck Hunting Gag: Holograms/ Fake it 'Til You Bake It
description: Ralph Phillips's daydreams get out of hand. Elmer falls victim to a high-tech hoax. Petunia is cooking up trouble.

title: Yosemite Samurai/ Bugs Hole Gags 2: Bees Nest/ Dummies in the Dark
description: Yosemite Sam is big in Japan. Elmer should "bee" more careful. It's lights out for Porky and Daffy.

title: Mummy Dummy/Telephone Pole Gags 2: Shrinking Telephone Pole/In The Road Again
description: Bugs meets a very old, very cranky mummy. Tweety spies a puddy from his perch. Wile E. Coyote gets stuck in asphalt.

title: Auto Birdy Shop/Daffy Traffic Cop Stop: Phone Booth/Eyes Wide Fudd
description: Tweety drives Sylvester crazy. Daffy runs a-fowl of the law. Elmer faces a trying trial.

title: Basketbugs/A Skate of Confusion!
description: Bugs Bunny plays some streetball. Porky Pig puts a new spin on an old sport: ice skating...with chainsaws.

title: Hide Out Hare/ Daffy Magician: An Ordinary Mop
description: Two gangsters regret hiding out in Bugs' rabbit hole. Porky regrets going to a magic show.

title: Funeral for A Fudd/  Love Goat
description: Elmer Fudd is a guest at his own funeral. Daffy's pet goat eats everything including Porky's wedding ring.
